Project: ReGen PEPT
Module: Home Page + Protocol Builder Deep Linking
Priority: High
Platform: Desktop first

Objective:
Add a new section on the home page to showcase a small set of high-scientific-evidence protocols. When the user clicks one of them, they must be redirected into the Protocol Builder with prefilled input data that makes that protocol clinically coherent and likely to be recommended.

Section name:
Evidence-Based Clinical Protocols

Primary business goal:
Use the homepage to surface clinically strong protocol examples and drive users directly into the Protocol Builder with realistic starting conditions.

Functional requirements:

1. Add a new homepage section below the main hero or in a visible mid-page position.
2. Title:
   Evidence-Based Clinical Protocols
3. Subtitle:
   Explore clinically structured pathways supported by current therapeutic rationale and protocol logic.
4. Show between 4 and 6 featured protocol cards.
5. Each card must include:
   - protocol title
   - primary clinical objective
   - main compounds
   - short scientific rationale
   - evidence badge
   - CTA button: “Open in Protocol Builder”

Protocol cards should be based on real protocol families already supported by Protocol Builder 2.0.

Initial recommended cards:
1. Structured Weight Management Protocol
2. Metabolic Optimization Protocol
3. Cognitive Support Protocol
4. Mitochondrial Energy Protocol
5. Skin & Aesthetics Protocol
6. Longevity Foundation Protocol

Card content requirements:

For each card show:
- Protocol title
- Clinical objective
- 1-line compound stack
- Short evidence rationale
- Evidence strength label

